history.content: CS 70 does not count toward your engineering units since it is a math class. This is the only EE/CS class with an exception like this to my knowledge. EE 126 and EE 127 are both engineering classes that count toward your 45 units.

I recently submitted a DARS Degree audit report, and noticed that, although I've taken CS 70, it didn't count towards Engineering/CS units. 

I was wondering if this was a mistake, and if it is not (presumably because either it is a lower div requirement or because it doesn't really teach "engineering" per se), do EE 126 and EE 127 (also mostly mathematical classes) count towards engineering units requirement?
history.subject: EECS Graduation "Engineering Units" requirement
